### PR-004

**Title**: Pino-based structured logger with trace_id correlation and per-tenant log scope
**Problem**: Today's logger is a bare `console.*`; `src/lib/consoleInterceptor.ts:1-80` patches `console.log` but the output is unstructured. When a user hits #4608, they get an HTML 502 page with no request ID.
**Solution**:
- Replace interceptors with a real `pino` instance + `pino-http`. Log format: NDJSON with `time`, `level`, `service`, `trace_id`, `span_id`, `request_id`, `route`, `method`, `status`, `duration_ms`, `provider.id`, `model.id`, `combo.id`, `tenant.id`, `user.id`, `error.kind`, `error.message`, `error.stack`.
- Async-local-storage-based context (`AsyncLocalStorage<RequestContext>`) so any function can grab the active `trace_id` without explicit threading.
- Files affected: `src/lib/observability/logger.ts` (new, 280 LOC), `src/lib/observability/context.ts` (new, 90 LOC), `src/lib/consoleInterceptor.ts:1-80` (deprecated, replaced), `src/lib/observability/logger-mw.ts` (new, 110 LOC), `src/server-init.ts:1-150` (mount), `package.json:200-240` (`pino`, `pino-http`, `pino-pretty` dev), `tests/unit/observability/logger.test.ts` (new, 200 LOC), `docs/observability/03-logging.md` (new, 110 LOC).
**Test plan**: Use `pino-test` to capture lines; verify each emitted log line contains `trace_id` matching the active span. Concurrent-request test verifies `AsyncLocalStorage` does not leak across requests.
**Risk**: Med — replaces existing logger; must be backwards-compatible with `consoleInterceptor` consumers.
**Estimate**: M

---

### PR-005

**Title**: Error tracking sink (Sentry-compatible envelope) with PII redaction
**Problem**: When #4714 (Claude tool message regression) and #4683 (Qoder jobToken) were filed, no stack trace was attached. We lack error aggregation.
**Solution**:
- Add a `SentryTransport`-shaped sink that posts to `SENTRY_DSN` if set. Falls back to a local file `data/errors.ndjson` (rotated at 50MB).
- Mandatory PII redaction: strip `Authorization`, `Cookie`, `x-api-key`, `*.token`, `*.password`, `*.secret`, `provider.credentials` before posting. Use `fast-redact` for pattern matching.
- Files affected: `src/lib/observability/errors.ts` (new, 240 LOC), `src/lib/observability/redact.ts` (new, 130 LOC), `src/lib/observability/sinks/sentry.ts` (new, 180 LOC), `src/lib/observability/sinks/file.ts` (new, 90 LOC), `src/lib/observability/sinks/noop.ts` (new, 20 LOC), `src/lib/errors/OmniRouteError.ts` (new typed error hierarchy, 110 LOC), `package.json:200-260` (`@sentry/node` optional), `tests/unit/observability/errors.test.ts` (new, 280 LOC), `tests/unit/observability/redact.test.ts` (new, 200 LOC), `docs/observability/04-errors.md` (new, 90 LOC).
**Test plan**: Synthesize errors with synthetic `Authorization: Bearer sk-test-xxx`, run through redactor, assert token absent. Send to a local mock Sentry server, assert envelope shape and stack trace.
**Risk**: Med — redaction mistakes leak credentials. Mandate 100% line-coverage on the redactor.
**Estimate**: M

---

### PR-006

**Title**: Distributed tracing of MCP/A2A protocol calls with W3C trace context propagation
**Problem**: OmniRoute advertises MCP and A2A support, but `src/lib/mcp` and `src/lib/a2a` exist with no tracing. When an MCP tool call fails, we have no link to the LLM call that triggered it.
**Solution**:
- Propagate `traceparent` (W3C) on every MCP tool request and A2A task delegation. Inject as `metadata.traceparent` on JSON-RPC envelopes.
- Add server-side span hierarchy: `omniroute.mcp.tool.call` → `omniroute.mcp.transport.roundtrip` → upstream.
- Files affected: `src/lib/mcp/client.ts:1-200` (instrumented), `src/lib/mcp/server.ts:1-200` (instrumented), `src/lib/a2a/dispatcher.ts:1-180` (instrumented), `src/lib/a2a/agent.ts:1-200` (instrumented), `src/lib/observability/propagators.ts` (new, 90 LOC), `tests/unit/observability/mcp-tracing.test.ts` (new, 220 LOC), `tests/unit/observability/a2a-tracing.test.ts` (new, 220 LOC), `docs/observability/05-mcp-a2a.md` (new, 80 LOC).
**Test plan**: Mock MCP server asserts it received `traceparent`. Mock A2A peer asserts `metadata.traceparent` on the request. Jaeger-style trace reconstruction in test.
**Risk**: Low.
**Estimate**: M

