### PR-007

**Title**: Live-tail log viewer in the dashboard with severity filter and trace search
**Problem**: When an operator opens an issue (like #4806 or #4802) they need to see logs in real-time. Today the dashboard has no log UI.
**Solution**:
- Add `GET /api/observability/logs?since=...&level=...&trace_id=...` returning NDJSON with cursor pagination. Backed by an in-memory ring buffer (default 10k lines) + optional tail of the on-disk `data/omniroute.log`.
- Add a React page `src/app/(dashboard)/observability/logs/page.tsx` with a virtualised list (`@tanstack/react-virtual`), a severity filter, a trace_id search box that highlights correlated log lines. Uses SSE to push new lines.
- Files affected: `src/app/api/observability/logs/route.ts` (new, 160 LOC), `src/app/api/observability/logs/stream/route.ts` (new, 110 LOC), `src/lib/observability/ringBuffer.ts` (new, 90 LOC), `src/app/(dashboard)/observability/logs/page.tsx` (new, 240 LOC), `src/app/(dashboard)/observability/logs/LogStream.tsx` (new, 200 LOC), `src/app/(dashboard)/observability/logs/SeverityFilter.tsx` (new, 100 LOC), `src/shared/components/observability/LogEntry.tsx` (new, 110 LOC), `tests/unit/observability/ringBuffer.test.ts` (new, 130 LOC), `tests/unit/api/observability-logs.test.ts` (new, 200 LOC), `tests/e2e/observability/logs.spec.ts` (Playwright, new, 180 LOC), `docs/observability/06-dashboard.md` (new, 80 LOC).
**Test plan**: Push 10k synthetic log lines, assert ring buffer is bounded and old lines evicted. Playwright test opens the page, asserts severity filter works, and verifies SSE delivery.
**Risk**: Med — exposes a log surface; redact secrets at the API boundary.
**Estimate**: L

