### PR-009

**Title**: Slow-query log and upstream latency heatmap
**Problem**: 502 bursts (#4252) and 300ms codex failures (#4602) need latency analysis across providers. Currently no histogram is computed.
**Solution**:
- Maintain a sliding window of per-upstream latencies (last 5 minutes, 1-second granularity) and compute p50/p95/p99.
- Add `src/app/(dashboard)/observability/latency/page.tsx` with a heatmap (x: provider, y: time bucket, color: p95).
- Emit `omniroute_upstream_latency_percentiles{provider,quantile}` (Prometheus Summary).
- Files affected: `src/lib/observability/latency.ts` (new, 230 LOC — fixed-cost circular buffer + percentile sketch), `src/lib/observability/metrics.ts:1-380` (add summary), `src/app/(dashboard)/observability/latency/page.tsx` (new, 180 LOC), `src/app/(dashboard)/observability/latency/Heatmap.tsx` (new, 220 LOC), `src/shared/components/charts/HeatmapCanvas.tsx` (new, 110 LOC), `src/app/api/observability/latency/route.ts` (new, 80 LOC), `tests/unit/observability/latency.test.ts` (new, 240 LOC), `tests/e2e/observability/latency.spec.ts` (new, 130 LOC), `docs/observability/08-latency.md` (new, 60 LOC).
**Test plan**: Synthetic load test, assert percentile values match ground truth within 5%. Playwright test asserts heatmap renders.
**Risk**: Med — fixed memory; must bound.
**Estimate**: M

